A vintage-style illustration depicting a crumbling, rust-covered desktop computer monitor from the early 2000s era, sitting abandoned on a dusty wooden desk. The monitor displays a frozen, glitchy screen with fragmented pixels and distorted colors. Around it, modern sleek devices like tablets and slim laptops float upward like ascending spirits, gleaming and pristine. Cobwebs stretch between the old monitor and the desk, while dust motes catch golden afternoon light streaming through a nearby window. The color palette contrasts warm sepia and brown tones for the obsolete technology against cool blues and silvers for the modern devices. The composition suggests technological evolution and the necessity of moving forward, with the old guard literally being left behind in shadow while progress rises toward the light.
